              Commentator7
              Albany, New York
              3935
              Reviewed March 2, 2020 via mobile
              Beautiful! Excellent Service!

              Chabil Mar is a collection of villas right on the beach in Placencia with beautiful gardens. Our villa, No. 10, was located right on the beach between two pools on the first floor. It has two bedrooms, a fully equipped kitchen, two baths, a veranda with table and chairs and a hammock. Chabil Mar is within walking distance to Palencia Village. There is a great bar and dining is delivered wherever you want it. The service, including the drivers (Lancho), the maids, the concierges and the bartenders (Ferdinand and Anselmo) and the waiters, was excellent. Chabil Mar offers different adventures. We enjoyed the Monkey River boat trip where we saw crocodiles, several birds, bats, Howler monkeys, iguanas and manatees. Our guide, Jason, was really nice and very knowledgeable. Lunch was served in the small village of Monkey River. We also went fishing. In addition we rented a car and drove south to Big Falls where we visited a Mayan family who educated us about Mayan cooking, plants and musical instruments.

              Date of stay: March 2020
              Trip type: Traveled as a couple
              Ask Commentator7 about Chabil Mar Guest Exclusive Resort

              Matthew B
              Saint Louis, Missouri
              812
              Reviewed February 26, 2020 via mobile
              Fantastic vacation!

              My wife and I just returned from a 4 night stay at Chabil Mar. It was our first time in Belize and we are already trying to schedule a return visit. The resort consists of 22 beautiful and independently decorated villas. It was very clean and comfortable and the food onsite was great. The fact you could drink the water was awesome as well. The resort grounds were immaculate. The best part of the resort was the staff. They were all so nice and attentive to our needs. Special props to Lacho, who was so helpful with local information and getting us back and forth from the village! We also really enjoyed the time GM Chris spent with us talking about the resort and the area. The resort was sold out during our stay but we felt like we had the whole resort to ourselves.

              The proximity to the village really contributed to our enjoyment on this trip. So many good watering holes and restaurants. Dawn’s, Wendy’s, and Tutti Fruiti were among our favorites!

              We would definitely recommend this resort to anyone interested in a peaceful, relaxing vacation at the beach!

              Date of stay: February 2020
              Trip type: Traveled as a couple

The reason is that our guests are taking advantage of sea, jungle and cultural tours every day or walking, biking or kayaking into the Village, out and about having a great time. And, as a boutique resort, as you mentioned, our beach and swimming pools are never crowded for that reason. When you did hang out with us for a relaxing time during the day or evening, we enjoyed serving you snacks, cocktails and meals out on the pier, the beach or pool.
